request.js
==========

[![NPM version](https://badge.fury.io/js/request.js.png)](https://npmjs.org/package/request.js)
[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/sonnyp/request.js.png?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/sonnyp/request.js)
[![Dependency Status](https://david-dm.org/sonnyp/request.js.png)](https://david-dm.org/sonnyp/request.js)
[![devDependency Status](https://david-dm.org/sonnyp/request.js/dev-status.png)](https://david-dm.org/sonnyp/request.js#info=devDependencies)

Simple and lightweight JavaScript library (Node.JS and browsers) to make HTTP requests.

```javascript
request({
    method: 'post',
    url: 'http://example.com',
    body: [{foo: 'bar'}, {'bar': foo}],
    headers: {
      'X-Powered-By': 'request.js'
    },
    username: 'foo',
    password: 'bar'
  },
  function(err, body) {

  },
  function(progress) {

  }
});
```

#### Support
|Engine       |Version|
|:-----------:|:-----:|
|Node.js      |≥ 0.8  |
|Chrome       |≥ 30   |
|Firefox      |≥ 23   |
|...?         |...?   |
